&gt;yep, they had etrade, sharebuilder (let you buy fractional shares), first trade was another one back then. It cost you i think about 5 dollars a trade and later you had a monthly fee. Fidelity you had to have 15k and some of the others a high amount as well. this was easy to ignore when everything was going up not so much post 1999.   
&gt;  
&gt;i invested everything in november of 1999 from my time in the military after a financial planning meeting. I went with communications, Lucent, qualcom, nokia, JDS uniphase and glw. I just remember a mutual fund i had went from 1000 dollars when i bought it to 200 dollars the next month.  I had about 10k worth of stock and it lost about half its value in the course of 3 months and kept going lower. I sold some and bough marvel comics which was around a 1 dollar a share after the release of the first x-men movie but they were risky due to flirting with bankruptcy yet again.  I did really well with my 500 dollars i bought sold at 23 dollars a share wish i kept it.  
&gt;  
&gt;  My dad sold his Apple stock about 50k worth  (he bought one year after the ipo) in 1992 to buy Marvel Stock which went bankrupt.
